		{"id":"c7ec9bd2d7d6bd36","type":"text","text":"OpenClaw负责文献批量阅读、实验数据初步分析","x":-125,"y":-30,"width":250,"height":60},
		{"id":"1634ad6e15bdbdc2","type":"text","text":"Claude Code负责代码编写、复杂数据分析、论文排版","x":-140,"y":140,"width":250,"height":60},
		{"id":"ae1370eadf188bba","type":"text","text":"在OpenClaw里调用Claude Code的API","x":160,"y":39,"width":250,"height":60},
		{"id":"45fe761b4672c352","type":"text","text":"To the Data Access Committee: \nI am writing to formally request access to the retinal imaging datasets provided by the Jacobs Retina Center at the University of California, San Diego. I am currently an Artificial Intelligence graduate student at Monash University, focusing on the intersection of Causal Inference and Medical Image Segmentation. \n\nMy interest in your dataset was sparked by the paper, Universal Vessel Segmentation for Multi-Modality Retinal Images. The domain shift problem across different retinal imaging modalities presents a significant bottleneck for the clinical deployment of segmentation models. \n\nMy current research aims to address this challenge by integrating causal inference mechanisms and Fourier Transform with advanced vision models. Access to the high-quality, multi-modality data from JRC would be strictly instrumental in this work. \n\nIn strict accordance with academic standards and ethical data usage policies, I formally declare the following regarding the use of the JRC dataset: Purpose: The data will be used exclusively for non-commercial, academic research purposes. \n\nData Security: The dataset will be stored securely on Monash University's computing infrastructure in Clayton. \nIt will not be shared, redistributed, or made accessible to unauthorized","x":-641,"y":481,"width":961,"height":499},
		{"id":"f6774e9a99f92816","type":"text","text":"python evaluate.py --datapath ./data/DRIVEN_test --note DRIVEN_test --seg_model Resdounet","x":760,"y":-100,"width":615,"height":99},
		{"id":"ffd97dd1b5064369","type":"text","text":"| **数据集 (Dataset)**   | **模型 (Model)**   | **Accuracy** | **Dice** | **SP (Specificity)** | **SE (Sensitivity)** | Pr  | **F1** | MCC | **clDice** | $\\beta_0$ | $\\beta_1$ |\n| ------------------- | ---------------- | ------------ | -------- | -------------------- | -------------------- | --- | ------ | --- | ---------- | --------- | --------- |\n| **JRCFA**           | Full model       | 0.9626       | 0.7297   | 0.9791               | 0.7480               |     | 0.7297 |     | 0.7600     |           |           |\n|                     | Topological only | 0.9705       | 0.7913   | 0.9823               | 0.8257               |     | 0.7913 |     | 0.8325     |           |           |\n| **JRCFAF**          | Full model       | 0.9731       | 0.7542   | 0.9797               | 0.8486               |     | 0.7542 |     | 0.8094     |           |           |\n|                     | Topological only | 0.9748       | 0.7575   | 0.9836               | 0.8073               |     | 0.7575 |     | 0.8182     |           |           |\n| **JRCIR**           | Full model       | 0.9639       | 0.7549   | 0.9798               | 0.7705               |     | 0.7549 |     | 0.7675     |           |           |\n|                     | Topological only | 0.9646       | 0.7524   | 0.9827               | 0.7442               |     | 0.7524 |     | 0.7648     |           |           |\n| **DRIVEN_training** | Full model       | 0.9650       | 0.7742   | 0.9878               | 0.7202               |     | 0.7742 |     | 0.7710     |           |           |\n|                     | Topological only | 0.9683       | 0.7937   | 0.9903               | 0.7320               |     | 0.7937 |     | 0.7993     |           |           |\n- **$\\beta_0$ (Betti-0 number)**\n    - **定义**：连通分量的数量\n    - **在血管分割中的意义**：理想情况下，血管网应该是连通的整体。如果 $\\beta_0$ 数值很大，说明预测的血管**断成了一截一截的碎块**\n    - **趋势**：数值越低代表血管连通性好\n        \n- **$\\beta_1$ (Betti-1 number)**\n    - **定义**：孔洞或环的数量\n    - **在血管分割中的意义**：代表血管网中形成的闭合环路。虽然正常的视网膜血管偶尔会有环路，但过高的 $\\beta_1$ 通常意味着模型在分割时，血管内部出现了**虚假的空心孔洞**\n    - **趋势**：数值越低代表分割结果内部填充实心、拓扑纯净","x":440,"y":69,"width":1215,"height":564},
		{"id":"c3acf019786f15b1","x":-762,"y":-230,"width":602,"height":510,"type":"text","text":"你是一个资深企业管理软件开发的全站程序员，目前你需要开发一个管理系统，满足以下生产场景：\n车间有一位“值班人员”，“值班人员”使用手机负责对当天加班的“工人”进行加班记录打卡。\n\n同时需要有一个管理员的后台，”管理人员“能够查询员工加班的详细记录，包括但不限于：\n- 每个“工人”的加班开始时间，结束时间，实际加班时长，每小时工资，人名，性别。\n- 月度，年度，加班时长总结。\n- 成本消耗分析\n更多组件扩展：\n- 能够导出exccel表格\n- 能够使用专业的图表可视化数据\n\n需要UI简洁，颜色为蓝白色调\n目前需要你给出一套整个项目开发的大致框架和详细细节，由我来评估\n\n\n# 功能细节补充\n- “值班人员”提交了一位“工人”的打工记录之后，”管理人员“需要在后台审核之后才会被标记为有效加班\n- 所有系统都在本地部署，出了手机端\n- 工人名单来源：“管理人员”在系统里手工录入\n- 加班时薪规则：需要“管理人员”手动录入倍率\n- 班组结构：由“管理人员”创建“值班人员”权限账号，根据账号确定权限\n- 历史记录修正：需要管理员能修改已完成的打卡时间（但是必须留痕）\n- 审核频率：需要实时通知（添加一个待处理消息箱，里面添加待处理信息）\n- 节假日判断：倍率由”管理人员“下拉选项选择（默认工作日）：分工作日 / 周末 / 节假日三档倍率，这些倍率可以自由更改"}
	],
	"edges":[]
}